<HEAD>President Lauds Japanese Emperor For Role In Ending WWII</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> WASHINGTON </LOCATION> _ President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> mourned the death of Emperor <PERSON> Hirohito </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, saying he played `` a truly heroic role'' in ending World War II hostilities between his country and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. `` On behalf of the people and government of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, we extend our deepest condolences to His Imperial Majesty, the Emperor, to the Imperial family, and to the <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION>,'' the president said in a statement released by the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> shortly after the annoucement of the emperor's death Friday. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said the emperor's 62-year reign `` spanned one of the most tumultuous, and yet at the same time constructive eras in the history of mankind _ an age of unprecedented economic collapse, a most vicious war, astonishing scientific acheivement, and dramatic political and social changes throughout the world.'' `` It was also an era of unprecedented reconciliation. His majesty played a truly heroic role in bringing hostilities between our two peoples to an end and leading the Japanese people through a period of reconstruction and reconciliation that has resulted in both the prosperity the Japanese know today and in the close relations our two nations and peoples now enjoy,'' <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said. The president recalled the late emperor had visited the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> in 1975, and that he and his wife <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> had `` enjoyed several meetings with him, most recently in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>'' in 1986. The statement also noted the first couple had entertained the former Crown Prince <PERSON> Akihito </PERSON> and Crown Princess <PERSON> Michiko <