of his father, <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> businessman <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Richter </PERSON>. Neither <PERSON> Richter </PERSON>'s father nor the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> have discussed how <PERSON> Richter </PERSON>'s release was achieved But the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> has insisted that the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government was not involved in the negotiations. Since his return from <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> has been free on a $ 250,000 bond signed by his father, and has worked for his father's business.
