<HEAD>Tremor Reported In Southwestern Franc</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TARBES, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 15-second tremor shook the mountainous southwestern region of <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>, but no injuries were reported, officials said Saturday. The quake, measuring 4.2 on the <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale, hit at 8:33 p.m. on Friday, said the officials. Its epicenter was at the ski station in <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mongie </LOCATION>, in the Pyrenees mountains that form the border between <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION>. The tremor reportedly caused some cracks in buildings and rattled furniture and other objects. The <PERSON> Richter </PERSON> scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on a seismograph. An earthquake of 3.5 can cause slight damage and one measuring 4 can cause moderate damage.
